{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-24T08:02:16.140394085Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-38050b7e","body":"`src/contexts/workflow_composition/final_review.rs:2458-2466` only retries when `is_timeout_related` or `is_transient_codex_failure` returns true, but `src/adapters/process_backend.rs:39-50` does not recognize `AppError::InvocationTimeout`. `AgentExecutionService` emits `InvocationTimeout` for both adapter-promoted timeouts and the service safety-net timeout (`src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs:259-264`, `395-410`), so reviewer and arbiter timeouts still fail immediately instead of using the transient retry loop.","dedup_key":"243f0b47187bf3b7b3627980d56bb2b3c7f4faa74c542bfb0d1eeea047e8b3c9","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260424065222","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":21,"timestamp":"2026-04-24T08:02:16.160958856Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-dc524dd6","body":"The vote phase is still single-shot. `src/contexts/workflow_composition/final_review.rs:986-1013` calls `invoke_final_review_member_once(...)` directly for `final_review:voter`, so a transient transport failure while collecting votes is still recorded as an immediate failure. On a minimum-quorum panel, one network blip during voting can still fail the whole final_review stage, which leaves the bead's reviewer-retry goal incomplete.","dedup_key":"5b72aefe28ef4eea12487e8a66c81692be5b3c9d1ded2ed5f43a8c6e44559245","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260424065222","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
